termbox
------------------------------------------
Termbox is a library that provides minimalistic API which allows the programmer
to write text-based user interfaces.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.10.0-1
  libtermbox1-1.1.2-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.31.0-1
  gcc-core-6.4.0-5
  gcc-g++-6.4.0-5
  python-2.7.14-1
  waf-1.5.19-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/nsf/termbox

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/nsf/termbox/archive/v1.1.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack termbox-1.1.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./termbox-1.1.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/termbox-1.1.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/termbox-1.1.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libtermbox1-1.1.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libtermbox-devel-1.1.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(termbox)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/termbox.README
  /usr/share/doc/termbox/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/termbox/README.md

(libtermbox1)
  /usr/bin/cygtermbox-1.dll

(libtermbox-devel)
  /usr/include/termbox.h
  /usr/lib/libtermbox.dll.a

------------------

